  "texts": [
    "Virtual patients can be used to simulate real-life medical scenarios and teach clinical reasoning and communication skills.",
    "A study by Potter et al.",
    "developed virtual patients using GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 for medical training on the Geeky Medics platform.",
    "Learners practiced communication and clinical reasoning through text or voice interactions and received AI-powered feedback.",
    "Despite some issues involving AI hallucinations and off-topic responses, the tool has had over 45,000 consultations, indicating high engagement and the potential to augment traditional clinical training [75]."
  ],
